---
import SiteShell from "../components/SiteShell.astro";
import "../styles/site.css";
---

<SiteShell
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Postmerce handles connected social accounts, uploaded media, publishing metadata and support requests."
  eyebrow="Legal"
>
  <section class="legal-prose">
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 3, 2026</p>

    <h2>Who operates Postmerce</h2>
    <p>
      Postmerce is operated by Triple Muffin. You can contact us at
      <a href="mailto:privacy@postmerce.pl">privacy@postmerce.pl</a> for privacy
      questions and <a href="mailto:support@postmerce.pl">support@postmerce.pl</a>
      for product support.
    </p>

    <h2>What Postmerce does</h2>
    <p>
      Postmerce lets authorized users upload video assets, prepare platform-specific
      captions and settings, schedule publishing jobs and review publication status
      across connected social accounts.
    </p>

    <h2>Data we process</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Account identity returned by connected platforms, such as channel, page or profile identifiers.</li>
      <li>OAuth tokens needed to publish on accounts explicitly connected by the user.</li>
      <li>Uploaded media, thumbnails, metadata, captions, hashtags, schedules and publishing options.</li>
      <li>Publishing status, error codes, retry information and sanitized API responses.</li>
      <li>Support messages sent to Postmerce email addresses.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use data</h2>
    <p>
      We use data only to provide the publishing workflow, maintain the service,
      troubleshoot publishing failures, improve reliability and respond to user
      requests. We do not sell personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>Social platform access</h2>
    <p>
      Postmerce connects to social platforms through OAuth. Users choose which
      accounts to connect and can revoke platform access in the platform settings.
      Tokens are stored encrypted and are not logged.
    </p>

    <h2>Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      Postmerce sends content and publishing metadata to the social platforms selected
      by the user. We may use infrastructure providers for hosting, DNS, security,
      email and storage. These providers process data only as needed to run the service.
    </p>

    <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Users can request deletion of connected account data, OAuth tokens, uploaded
      media and publishing metadata. See <a href="/data-deletion">Data deletion</a>
      for instructions.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use encrypted transport, encrypted OAuth token storage, private server access
      and least-privilege platform scopes where possible. No internet service is risk
      free, but we design Postmerce to avoid exposing secrets and unnecessary data.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as Postmerce evolves. The date above shows the latest
      published version.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteShell>
